    dc:description "FIGURE 29A–H. Seira barrai sp. nov.: A, subcoxa I; B, subcoxa II; C, subcoxa III; D, trochanteral organ; E, distal tibiotarsus and empodial complex III (posterior view); F, collophore chaetotaxy (lateral view); G, manubrium ventral chaetotaxy, arrows indicate elongated apical scales and supapical ciliate chaeta, respectively; H, manubrial plate and subapical chaetae (dorsal view)." ;
